P2P Cycle Stages Simulated
Demand Management (Sales Order / PIR)
        ↓
MRP Run (MD01) → BOM Explosion + Net Requirements
        ↓
Planned Orders → System-Generated Proposals
        ↓
Production Order (CO01) → Release
        ↓
Goods Issue (MIGO) → Issue RM from Warehouse [Mvt Type 261]
        ↓
Production Execution → Work Centers (8 Routing Steps)
        ↓
Order Confirmation (CO11N) → Qty, Time, Scrap per Operation
        ↓
Goods Receipt (MB31) → FG into Stock [Mvt Type 101]
        ↓
Order Settlement (KO88) → Variance Analysis

Key Learnings

Understanding of SAP PP module structure and transactions
Multi-level BOM explosion and MRP calculation logic
Production order lifecycle from creation to settlement
Work center capacity planning and routing definition
Material movement types (261 – GI, 101 – GR)
Production KPI dashboard design in Excel
